.env
app/.env
app/node_modules/
app/ios/
app/android/
app/.expo/
__pycache__/
.venv/
# Evidence artifacts ARE tracked — BAKEOFF-RESULT.md cites them, and an
# uncheckable citation is the exact defect Codex #9 caught (the smoke-run trail).
out/*
!out/q1.json
!out/q2.json
!out/.gitignore

# The live app is a symlink to ~/bakeoff-app (outside the repo) because Expo's
# EXConstants build script is not space-safe and every path here has spaces.
# The reviewed source lives in spike/app-src/. Codex #10 correctly noted git
# cannot prove which executable/dependency tree produced the evidence — an
# accepted limitation of a closed throwaway spike, not a live risk.
app
backup/
